<p>North Korea launched suspected short-range ballistic missiles on Tuesday from an area near Pyongyang toward waters off its east coast, according to South Korea and Japan. Japanese authorities said at least one object believed to be a ballistic missile fell into the sea. The launches drew condemnation from South Korea and Japan and came as Seoul and Washington discussed adjusting their joint defense posture, while the U.S. outlined a new defense strategy referenced in some reporting.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/ueu14_gzxA5SbE5HsfIKLiDj6shZaPJYCjJuIFzWTHUxuqbHCOL3iqEVtZYL7nKsG7bK_WEOw-_8dLWnU8rvo6GHNenKeHVzWvWqdWKYK677DwXKuZsWKURP4rkY7PqgZw2e9ptbWM2iUAfPi3YFoaV81Gkn6W-0ZuxpCnAYvxfzmQ' alt='Thumbnail image used with Firstpost report on North Korea missile launches.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Launch site: South Korea’s military said multiple ballistic missiles were fired from north of Pyongyang.</li><li>Tokyo notice: Japan’s government and maritime authorities issued alerts as the launch was detected and assessed to have fallen into the sea.</li><li>Analyst view: One account said analysts see the tests as part of a push for better precision-strike performance and potential future exports, including to Russia.</li><li>Alliance planning: The missile activity coincided with Seoul–Washington talks on reshaping their combined defense posture toward North Korea.</li><li>Wider tensions: Regional reporting framed the launches as occurring amid heightened animosity between North and South Korea.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>South Korea: Seoul publicly reported the launches and treated them as an unidentified projectile/missile event requiring assessment and coordination. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/south-korea-north-korea-launched-unidentified-projectile-sea-129589072'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Japan: Japan’s coast guard said an object suspected to be a ballistic missile likely fell into the sea, reflecting its focus on maritime safety and warning systems. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3341463/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missiles-us-signals-defence-shift'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>North Korea (as assessed by analysts): Analysts cited in reporting said the tests align with efforts to improve precision-strike capability and to test systems potentially meant for export. (<a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missile-south-korea-japan-updates/article70555685.ece'>The Hindu</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missile-south-korea-japan-updates/article70555685.ece'>North Korea fires ballistic missile towards Sea of Japan: Tokyo</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/north-korea-launches-missiles-into-sea-as-discussions-continue-over-us-defence-presence-13973130.html'>North Korea launches missiles into sea as discussions continue over US defence presence</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://japantoday.com/category/world/south-korea-says-north-korea-has-launched-an-unidentified-projectile-toward-the-sea1'>North Korea launches suspected ballistic missiles toward the sea, neighbors say</a> - japantoday.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/asia/east-asia/article/3341463/north-korea-fires-ballistic-missiles-us-signals-defence-shift'>North Korea fires ballistic missiles as US signals defence shift</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/south-korea-north-korea-launched-unidentified-projectile-sea-129589072'>South Korea says North Korea has launched an unidentified projectile toward the sea</a> - abcnews.go.com</li></ul>